endpointAlgorithms.name: Primary: Progression-Free Survival (PFS)
inputs: Date of first occurrence of disease progression (RECIST v1.1)
Date of death from any cause

timeWindow.duration: Until first occurrence of disease progression or death

endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: min(Date of disease progression, Date of death) - Date of randomization. If no event, censor at last tumor assessment date. If no post-baseline assessment, censor at Date of randomization + 1 day.
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Statistically significant improvement in PFS compared to placebo arm based on stratified log-rank test (alpha = 0.05) following hierarchical testing order.
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: Progression-free survival (PFS), defined as the time from randomisation to the first occurrence of disease progression, as determined by the investigator using RECIST v1.1, or death from any cause dur

endpointAlgorithms.name: Secondary: Overall Survival (OS)
inputs: Date of death from any cause
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: Date of death - Date of randomization
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Statistically significant improvement in OS compared to placebo arm, tested hierarchically after PFS.
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: overall survival (OS) in the PD-L1-positive subpopulation; [4] OS in the ITT population

endpointAlgorithms.name: Secondary: Objective Response Rate (ORR)
inputs: Number of patients with objective response (CR or PR)
Total number of patients in subpopulation
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: (Patients with confirmed Complete Response [CR] or Partial Response [PR]) / (Total patients in evaluable population)
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Higher proportion of responders in atezolizumab arm compared to placebo arm.
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: ORR by RECIST v1.1 in the PD-L1-positive, Response-evaluable subpopulation; [6] ORR by RECIST v1.1 in the ITT population.

endpointAlgorithms.name: Secondary: Time to Deterioration in Global Health Status
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: Time from randomization to first decrease in Global Health Status score (threshold typically defined in SAP)
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Delayed time to deterioration compared to placebo arm.
endpointAlgorithms.sourceText: Time to deterioration in Global Health Status

endpointAlgorithms.name: Secondary: Clinical Benefit Rate (CBR)
endpointAlgorithms.algorithm: (Patients with CR + PR + Stable Disease [SD] of specific duration) / (Total patients)
endpointAlgorithms.successCriteria: Higher proportion of patients with clinical benefit in treatment arm.

derivedVariables.name: Overall Survival
derivedVariables.derivationRule: Date of death from any cause minus date of randomization
derivedVariables.imputationRule: Censored at date last known to be alive

derivedVariables.name: Time to deterioration in Global Health Status
sourceVariables: EORTC QLQ-C30 Global Health Status score
derivedVariables.derivationRule: Time from randomization to the first decrease in GHS score of at least 10 points from baseline
derivedVariables.baselineDefinition: Last non-missing assessment prior to first dose
derivedVariables.imputationRule: Censored at last valid PRO assessment

derivedVariables.name: Progression-Free Survival
derivedVariables.derivationRule: Time from randomization to the first occurrence of disease progression or death from any cause
derivedVariables.analysisWindow: From randomization until progression or death

derivedVariables.name: Objective Response Rate
derivedVariables.derivationRule: Proportion of patients with a best overall response of Complete Response (CR) or Partial Response (PR)
derivedVariables.baselineDefinition: Presence of measurable disease at baseline

derivedVariables.name: Duration of Objective Response
sourceVariables: Date of first CR or PR
derivedVariables.derivationRule: Time from first documented response (CR or PR) to first documented disease progression or death
derivedVariables.baselineDefinition: First occurrence of CR or PR
derivedVariables.analysisWindow: From first response until progression or death

derivedVariables.name: Clinical Benefit Rate
derivedVariables.derivationRule: Proportion of patients with CR, PR, or Stable Disease (SD) lasting at least 6 months
derivedVariables.baselineDefinition: Presence of measurable or evaluable disease at baseline

derivedVariables.name: Changes from Baseline in Patient Function and Symptoms
derivedVariables.baselineDefinition: Last non-missing assessment prior to first dose
derivedVariables.imputationRule: MMRM or as specified in the SAP
